## Phase 4: Changelog Layout Restructure

### Overview
Follow the blog pattern: make `changelog/layout.tsx` a bare pass-through, move the "Changelog" heading + RSS link into the listing page, and have the entry page own its own centering.

### Changes Required:

#### 1. Simplify Changelog Layout

**File**: `apps/www/src/app/(app)/(marketing)/(content)/changelog/layout.tsx`

Replace the current layout (which renders heading, RSS, and constrains width) with a bare pass-through matching `blog/layout.tsx`:

```tsx
export default function ChangelogLayout({
  children,
}: {
  children: React.ReactNode;
}) {
  return <div className="min-h-screen">{children}</div>;
}
```

#### 2. Move Heading + RSS into Listing Page

**File**: `apps/www/src/app/(app)/(marketing)/(content)/changelog/page.tsx`

Wrap the existing content in the centering container and add the heading + RSS link that was previously in the layout. The listing page currently renders inside the layout's `max-w-2xl` container — now it must own that itself.

The `return` block becomes:

```tsx
return (
  <>
    <JsonLd code={structuredData} />
    <div className="mx-auto w-full min-w-0 max-w-2xl pt-24 pb-32">
      <div className="mb-12 flex items-center justify-between">
        <h1 className="font-medium font-pp text-3xl text-foreground">
          Changelog
        </h1>
        <NavLink
          className="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-muted-foreground text-sm transition-colors hover:text-foreground"
          href={"/changelog/rss.xml" as Route}
          title="Subscribe to RSS Feed"
        >
          <RssIcon className="h-4 w-4" />
          <span>RSS Feed</span>
        </NavLink>
      </div>
      <div className="space-y-12 text-foreground">
        {/* ... existing sortedPages.map content unchanged ... */}
      </div>
    </div>
  </>
);
```

Add the necessary imports to `changelog/page.tsx`:

```typescript
import { RssIcon } from "lucide-react";
import type { Route } from "next";
```

(`NavLink` is already imported.)

#### 3. Entry Page Owns Its Own Centering

**File**: `apps/www/src/app/(app)/(marketing)/(content)/changelog/[slug]/page.tsx`

Wrap the existing `<article>` in the centering container that was previously provided by the layout:

```tsx
return (
  <>
    <JsonLd code={jsonLd} />
    <article className="mx-auto w-full max-w-2xl space-y-3 pt-24 pb-32">
      {/* ... existing article content unchanged ... */}
    </article>
  </>
);
```

The `<article>` currently has `className="space-y-3"` — merge the centering classes into it: `className="mx-auto w-full max-w-2xl space-y-3 pt-24 pb-32"`.

